msgid "An online tour of the changes in Xfce 4.16 can be viewed here:\n"
msgstr "En onlinerundvisning over ændringerne i Xfce 4.16 kan ses her:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1608595200.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "A detailed overview of the changes between Xfce 4.14 and Xfce 4.16 releases can be found on the following page:\n"
msgstr "Et detaljeret overblik over ændringerne mellem Xfce 4.14 og Xfce 4.16 findes på følgende side:\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.14 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.14 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Today, after 4 years and 5 months of work, we are pleased to announce the release of the Xfce desktop 4.14, a new stable version that supersedes Xfce 4.12.\n"
msgstr "I dag, efter 4 år og 5 måneders arbejde, er vi glade for at kunne bekendtgøre udgivelsen af Xfce-skrivebordet 4.14, en ny stabil version som afløser Xfce 4.12.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this 4.14 cycle the main goal was to port all core components to Gtk3 (over Gtk2) and GDBus (over D-Bus GLib). Most components also received GObject Introspection support. Along the way we ended up polishing our user experience, introducing quite a few new features and improvements (read below) and fixings a boatload of bugs (read changelog).\n"
msgstr "In this 4.14 cycle the main goal was to port all core components to Gtk3 (over Gtk2) and GDBus (over D-Bus GLib). Most components also received GObject Introspection support. Along the way we ended up polishing our user experience, introducing quite a few new features and improvements (read below) and fixings a boatload of bugs (read changelog).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **main highlights of this release** are:\n"
msgstr "The **main highlights of this release** are:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [window manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfwm4/start) received a slew of updates and features, including support for VSync (using either Present or OpenGL as backend) to reduce or remove display flickering, HiDPI support, improved GLX support with NVIDIA proprietary/closed source drivers, support for XInput2, various compositor improvements and a new default theme.\n"
msgstr "The [window manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfwm4/start) received a slew of updates and features, including support for VSync (using either Present or OpenGL as backend) to reduce or remove display flickering, HiDPI support, improved GLX support with NVIDIA proprietary/closed source drivers, support for XInput2, various compositor improvements and a new default theme.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [panel](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-panel/start) got support for RandR's primary monitor feature, improved window grouping in the tasklist plugin (better UX, visual group indicator etc), a per-panel \"icon-size\" setting, a new default clock format and clock format evaluator as well as an improved default panel layout.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [desktop](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfdesktop/start) now has support for RandR's primary monitor feature, an orientation option for icon arrangement, a \"Next Background\" context menu option to advance the wallpaper and it now syncs the user's wallpaper selection to AccountsService.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "A completely new settings dialog to [manage color profiles](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/color) has been created. For most users this means out of the box support for color-managed printing (through cupsd) and scanning (through saned). For monitor profiles you will have to install an additional service like xiccd.\n"
msgstr "A completely new settings dialog to [manage color profiles](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/color) has been created. For most users this means out of the box support for color-managed printing (through cupsd) and scanning (through saned). For monitor profiles you will have to install an additional service like xiccd.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [display dialog](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/display) received a lot of attention during this cycle and a big feature: Users are now able to save and (automatically) restore complete multi-display configurations, which is especially helpful for those who frequently connect their laptop to varying docking stations or setups. Furthermore a lot of time was spent on making the user interface more intuitive and a hidden option was added to support RandR display scaling (configured via Xfconf).\n"
msgstr "The [display dialog](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/display) received a lot of attention during this cycle and a big feature: Users are now able to save and (automatically) restore complete multi-display configurations, which is especially helpful for those who frequently connect their laptop to varying docking stations or setups. Furthermore a lot of time was spent on making the user interface more intuitive and a hidden option was added to support RandR display scaling (configured via Xfconf).\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "We added an option to enable Gtk window scaling to the [appearance dialog](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/appearance) and a monospace font option as well. However we had to drop theme previews as they didn't produce consistent results with Gtk3.\n"
msgstr "We added an option to enable Gtk window scaling to the [appearance dialog](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/appearance) and a monospace font option as well. However we had to drop theme previews as they didn't produce consistent results with Gtk3.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "While we decided to drop splash screens from the [session manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-session/start), we added lots of features and fixes instead. Among them are hybrid sleep support, improvements to the default session startup avoiding race conditions, a feature to add and edit autostart entries, a switch user button in the logout dialog and improved session chooser and settings dialogs (the latter with a new tab that shows saved sessions). Furthermore you can now run commands not only \"autostart style\" at login time, but also when your computer suspends, logs out etc. Finally Gtk applications are now session-managed over DBus and screensavers are also communicated with (e.g. inhibited) over DBus.\n"
msgstr "While we decided to drop splash screens from the [session manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-session/start), we added lots of features and fixes instead. Among them are hybrid sleep support, improvements to the default session startup avoiding race conditions, a feature to add and edit autostart entries, a switch user button in the logout dialog and improved session chooser and settings dialogs (the latter with a new tab that shows saved sessions). Furthermore you can now run commands not only \"autostart style\" at login time, but also when your computer suspends, logs out etc. Finally Gtk applications are now session-managed over DBus and screensavers are also communicated with (e.g. inhibited) over DBus.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "As always, [Thunar](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/start) - our file manager - received a lot of features and fixes. Among the visible changes are the completely reworked pathbar, support for larger thumbnails as well as support for a \"folder.jpg\" file altering the folder's icon (e.g. for music album covers). Power users will also notice the improved keyboard navigation (zooming, tab navigation). Thunar's volume manager has gained Bluray support.\n"
msgstr "As always, [Thunar](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/start) - our file manager - received a lot of features and fixes. Among the visible changes are the completely reworked pathbar, support for larger thumbnails as well as support for a \"folder.jpg\" file altering the folder's icon (e.g. for music album covers). Power users will also notice the improved keyboard navigation (zooming, tab navigation). Thunar's volume manager has gained Bluray support.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our [thumbnailing service tumbler](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/tumbler) received a lot of fixes and support for the Fujifilm RAF format.\n"
msgstr "Our [thumbnailing service tumbler](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/tumbler) received a lot of fixes and support for the Fujifilm RAF format.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [application finder](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-appfinder/start) can now optionally be opened as a single window and can now be more easily navigated with the keyboard only.\n"
msgstr "The [application finder](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-appfinder/start) can now optionally be opened as a single window and can now be more easily navigated with the keyboard only.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [power manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-power-manager/start) received a lot of bugfixes and some smaller features, including support for the XF86Battery button and for the newly created xfce4-screensaver. The panel plugin also saw several improvements: it can now optionally show the remaining time and/or percentage and it now relies on UPower's standard icon names to work with more icon themes out of the box. With LXDE moving on to a QT base the LXDE panel plugin was dropped.\n"
msgstr "The [power manager](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-power-manager/start) received a lot of bugfixes and some smaller features, including support for the XF86Battery button and for the newly created xfce4-screensaver. The panel plugin also saw several improvements: it can now optionally show the remaining time and/or percentage and it now relies on UPower's standard icon names to work with more icon themes out of the box. With LXDE moving on to a QT base the LXDE panel plugin was dropped.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "A lot of **applications and plugins** that are part of the Xfce eco-system - often dubbed \"goodies\" - are part of what makes Xfce great. A lot of those have also seen important changes along the timeline of the 4.14 release. To highlight a few:\n"
msgstr "A lot of **applications and plugins** that are part of the Xfce eco-system - often dubbed \"goodies\" - are part of what makes Xfce great. A lot of those have also seen important changes along the timeline of the 4.14 release. To highlight a few:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our [notification service](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/notifyd/start) has gained support for persistence - in other words: notification logging - and a \"Do Not Disturb\" mode, which suppresses all notifications. A new panel plugin was created that shows missed notifications (especially helpful during \"Do Not Disturb\" mode) and gives quick access to toggling \"Do Not Disturb\" mode. Finally support for showing notifications on RandR's primary monitor was added.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our media player [Parole](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/parole/start) received improved support for network streams and podcasts, as well as a new \"mini mode\" and automatic choosing of the best available video backend. Furthermore it also inhibits both screensavers and power managers during video playback now, making sure users don't have to go wiggle their mouse periodically while enjoying a movie.\n"
msgstr "Our media player [Parole](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/parole/start) received improved support for network streams and podcasts, as well as a new \"mini mode\" and automatic choosing of the best available video backend. Furthermore it also inhibits both screensavers and power managers during video playback now, making sure users don't have to go wiggle their mouse periodically while enjoying a movie.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our image viewer [Ristretto](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/ristretto/start) has seen various user interface improvements and support for setting the desktop wallpaper. It has recently also seen its first Gtk3-based development release.\n"
msgstr "Our image viewer [Ristretto](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/ristretto/start) has seen various user interface improvements and support for setting the desktop wallpaper. It has recently also seen its first Gtk3-based development release.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [screenshooter](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screenshooter/start) now allows users to move the selection rectangle and at the same time displays its width and height. The imgur upload dialog was revamped and the command line allows for more flexibility.\n"
msgstr "The [screenshooter](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screenshooter/start) now allows users to move the selection rectangle and at the same time displays its width and height. The imgur upload dialog was revamped and the command line allows for more flexibility.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our [clipboard manager](https://docs.xfce.org/panel-plugins/clipman/start) now has improved keyboard shortcut support (through a port to GtkApplication), improved and more consistent icon sizing as well as a new application icon.\n"
msgstr "Our [clipboard manager](https://docs.xfce.org/panel-plugins/clipman/start) now has improved keyboard shortcut support (through a port to GtkApplication), improved and more consistent icon sizing as well as a new application icon.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [pulseaudio panel plugin](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/pulseaudio-plugin/start) received MPRIS2 support to be able to remotely control media players and desktop-wide multimedia key support, essentially rendering xfce4-volumed-pulse a superfluous additional daemon.\n"
msgstr "The [pulseaudio panel plugin](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/pulseaudio-plugin/start) received MPRIS2 support to be able to remotely control media players and desktop-wide multimedia key support, essentially rendering xfce4-volumed-pulse a superfluous additional daemon.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "And finally the [terminal emulator](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/terminal/start) saw a huge amount of bug fixes and improvements since Xfce 4.12.\n"
msgstr "And finally the [terminal emulator](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/terminal/start) saw a huge amount of bug fixes and improvements since Xfce 4.12.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is also a group of **new projects** that have become part of our project. Say hi to:\n"
msgstr "There is also a group of **new projects** that have become part of our project. Say hi to:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "We finally have our own [screensaver](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screensaver/start) (yes - we realize it's 2019 ;)). With lots of features and tight Xfce integration (obviously) it is a great addition to our catalog.\n"
msgstr "We finally have our own [screensaver](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screensaver/start) (yes - we realize it's 2019 ;)). With lots of features and tight Xfce integration (obviously) it is a great addition to our catalog.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [status notifier panel plugin](https://goodies.xfce.org/projects/panel-plugins/xfce4-statusnotifier-plugin) provides a next-generation system tray where applications can show indicators. It supersedes the Ubuntu-centric xfce4-indicator-plugin for most application indicators.\n"
msgstr "The [status notifier panel plugin](https://goodies.xfce.org/projects/panel-plugins/xfce4-statusnotifier-plugin) provides a next-generation system tray where applications can show indicators. It supersedes the Ubuntu-centric xfce4-indicator-plugin for most application indicators.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Catfish file search](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/catfish/start) is like an old friend for most Xfce users - now it's officially part of Xfce!\n"
msgstr "[Catfish file search](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/catfish/start) is like an old friend for most Xfce users - now it's officially part of Xfce!\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finally [Panel Profiles](https://git.xfce.org/apps/xfce4-panel-profiles/about/), which allows you to backup and restore your panel layouts, has moved under the Xfce umbrella.\n"
msgstr "Finally [Panel Profiles](https://git.xfce.org/apps/xfce4-panel-profiles/about/), which allows you to backup and restore your panel layouts, has moved under the Xfce umbrella.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "As always it’s also time to say goodbye to some older **unmaintained or deprecated projects**. (Luckily our projects only go to the attic aka the archive on git.xfce.org when they die.) With a salty teardrop of sadness we bid farewell to:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "garcon-vala, gtk-xfce-engine, pyxfce, thunar-actions-plugin, xfbib, xfc, xfce4-kbdleds-plugin, xfce4-mm, xfce4-taskbar-plugin, xfce4-windowlist-plugin, xfce4-wmdock-plugin and xfswitch-plugin\n"
msgstr "garcon-vala, gtk-xfce-engine, pyxfce, thunar-actions-plugin, xfbib, xfc, xfce4-kbdleds-plugin, xfce4-mm, xfce4-taskbar-plugin, xfce4-windowlist-plugin, xfce4-wmdock-plugin and xfswitch-plugin\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "An online tour of the changes in Xfce 4.14 can be viewed here:\n"
msgstr "En onlinerundvisning over ændringerne i Xfce 4.14 kan ses her:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1565568000.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "A detailed overview of the changes between Xfce 4.12 and Xfce 4.14 releases can be found on the following page:\n"
msgstr "Et detaljeret overblik over ændringerne mellem Xfce 4.12 og Xfce 4.14 findes på følgende side:\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.12 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.12 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.12 is be the best release ever (yes, we like to party!)!\n"
msgstr "Xfce 4.12 er den bedste udgivelse nogensinde (ja, vi er i festhumør!)!\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Source : Internet comments.\n"
msgstr "Kilde : Internet-kommentarer.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Today, after 2 years and 10 months of work, we are pleased to announce the release of the Xfce desktop 4.12, a new stable version that supersedes Xfce 4.10.\n"
msgstr "I dag, efter 2 år og 10 måneders arbejde, er vi glade for at kunne bekendtgøre udgivelsen af Xfce-skrivebordet 4.12, en ny stabil version som afløser Xfce 4.10.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "This long period can only be explained by how awesome Xfce 4.10 was. But as all things, it needed some refreshing - and for that we saw lots of new contributors providing valuable feedback, features and bugfixes. As always, Xfce follows its steady pace of evolution without revolution that seems to match our users' needs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this 4.12 cycle, we mainly focused on polishing our user experience on the desktop and window manager, and on updating some components to take advantage of newly available technologies.\n"
msgstr "I denne 4.14 cyklus, fokuserer vi primært på at polere vores bruger-oplevelse på skrivebordet og vindue-bestyren, og på at opdatere nogle komponenter til at tage fordel af nye tilgængelige teknologier.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "The main highlights of this release are:\n"
msgstr "De primære højdepunkter at denne udgivelse er:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The window manager gained a new themable Alt+Tab dialog with optional windows preview and a list mode. Initial Client side decoration support was implemented, window tiling mode was improved providing support for corner-tiling, and a new zooming mode was added. A HiDPI Xfwm theme was also added.\n"
msgstr "Vindue-håndtering fik nyt tema-redigerbart Alt+Tab dialog med muligheden vindue-forhåndsvisning og en liste-metode. Den første klient-side dekorations understøttelse var implementeret, vindue-flise-metoden var forbedret, tilbyder nu understøttelse for hjørne-flisning, og en ny zoome-metode var tilføjet. En HiDPI Xfwm tema var også inkluderet.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The panel can now intelligently hide itself, supports Gtk3 plugins, and saw lots of its third-party plugins updated to take full advantage of the features added in 4.10.\n"
msgstr "Panelet kan nu med intelligens gemme sig selv, understøtter Gtk4 plugins, og så mange af dets tredjepart plugin opdateret til at tage fuld fordel af funktionerne tilføjet i 4.10.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The desktop has a new wallpaper settings dialog, per workspace wallpaper support, and better multi-monitor handling. It also supports displaying folder cover art and emblems on icons now.\n"
msgstr "Skrivebordet har en ny baggrunds-indstillings dialog, hver arbejdsplads baggrunds-billede understøttelse, og bedre fler-skærms håndtering. Det understøtter også at vise mappe-omslag or emblemer på ikoner nu.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our session manager was updated to use logind and/or upower if available for hibernate/suspend support. For portability and to respect our users' choices, fallback modes were implemented relying on os-specific backends.\n"
msgstr "Vores session-håndtering var opdateret til at bruge logind og/eller upower hvis tilgængelig for dvale/suspenderings understøttelse. For bærbarhed og for at respektere vores brugers valg, fald-tilbage indstilling var implementeret ved at regne med os-specifikte bagender.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Support for multi-monitor use was improved in a new display settings dialog and a quick setup popup on monitor plugging.\n"
msgstr "Understøttelse for fler-skærmsbrug var forbedret i en ny viser-indstillings dialog og en hurtig opsætnings-popup på skærm tilslutning.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The appearance dialog now showcases previews for icons and themes.\n"
msgstr "Udseende-dialogen udviser nu forhåndsvisning af ikoner og temaer.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfsettingsd now supports libinput.\n"
msgstr "Xfsettingsd understøtter nu libinput.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Power management was not forgotten: A new panel plugin was created, logind/upower support was added to handle battery/lid/brightness events, and locking via light-locker was implemented. The settings dialog was also revamped, and support for X11 screenblanking was added.\n"
msgstr "Strømstyring var ikke glemt: Et nyt panel plugin var skabt, logind/upower understøttelse var tilføjet for at håndtere batteri/låg/lysstyrke tilfælde, og låser gennem lys-låser var implementeret. Indstillings-dialogen var også moderniseret, og understøttelse af X11 skærm-blankning var tilføjet.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our file manager, the beloved Thunar, saw an insane amount of improvements: tab support, tons of bug fixes, speed-ups, key shortcuts for custom actions, better naming of file copies and links, nice freespace bar in properties, tweaks for the renamer and other dialogs, improved keyboard navigation, fixes for the treeview pane, better wallpaper support, Gtk3 bookmarks support, multiple file properties... need we say more?\n"
msgstr "Vores fil-håndterer, vores elskede Thunar, så et sindssygt antal af forbedringer: tab understøttelse, tonsvis af fejlretninger, hastigheds-forbedringer, tastatur genveje for brugerdefinerede handlinger, bedre navne-givning af fil kopier og links, dejlige gratisplads-bar i indstillinger, forbedringer til navne-redigeren og andre dialoger, forbedret tastatur navigation, fejlretninger af træ-udsigt panelet, bedre baggrundsbillede understøttelse, Gtk3 bogmærke understøttelse, flere fil-indstillinger ... Behøver vi sige mere?\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "To prepare the future of Xfce with Gtk3, which no longer requires theme engines, we are stopping the development of our Gtk theme engine, and dropping our Gtk3 engine - theme makers, please update your themes to CSS if you want them to work on the next Xfce version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Due to gstreamer1.0 having dropped the mixer-interface entirely, and xfce4-mixer and xfce4-volumed relying on this interface with gstreamer0.10, our mixer application and volume daemon cannot be ported to 1.0 and are consequently not maintained anymore.\n"
msgstr "Fordi gstreamer1.0 har droppet mikser-brugergrænsefladen helt, og xfce4-mikseren og xfce4-volumed kræver denne grænseflade med gstreamer0.10, vores mikser appllikation og lyddstyrkedæmon kan ikke porteres til 1.0 og er deraf ikke vedligeholdt længere.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce wouldn't be what it is right now without all its goodies. In this area, we also saw a flurry of activity, most notably:\n"
msgstr "Xfce ville ikke være hvad det var nu, uden alle dets lækkerier. På dette område, så vi også en byge af aktivitet, mest især:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfburn gained BluRay Disc burning support.\n"
msgstr "Xfburn har fået BluRay Disk brænding understøttelse.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Task manager UI was totally revamped, and got ported to Gtk3.\n"
msgstr "Job-liste UI var total omskrevet og blev porteret til Gtk3.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Parole's UI was totally redone, parts of it rewritten with many features added. Furthermore it was ported to Gtk3 and gstreamer1.0.\n"
msgstr "Parole's UI var total omskrevet, dele af den omskrevet med mange funktioner tilføjet. Derudover var den porteret til Gtk3 og gstreamer1.0.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mousepad was totally rewritten and got an initial port to Gtk3.\n"
msgstr "Muse-redskab var total omskrevet og fik en første port til Gtk3.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Imgur.com support was added to the screenshooter.\n"
msgstr "imgur.com undersøttelse var tilføjet til skærmbillede-tageren.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new GNOME-Shell-like dashboard named xfdashboard is now available.\n"
msgstr "En ny GNOME-Shell-lignende instrumentbræt navngivet xfinstrumentbræt er nu tilgængelig.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new alternative menu for the panel named whiskermenu was added.\n"
msgstr "En ny alternativ menu for panelet kaldet whiskermenu var tilføjet.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "The GNOME2 hardware monitor plugin was ported to our panel.\n"
msgstr "GNOME2 hardware overvågnings-plugin var porteret til vores panel.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Weather plugin got a totally new user interface with powerful customization options and provides tons of detailed information.\n"
msgstr "Vejr-pluginet fik en total ny brugergrænseflade med kraftig brugerdefinerings-muligheder og giver tonsvis af detaljerede information.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Eyes plugin uses 3D coordinates to calculate its eye position, so even more sometimes scary, sometimes funny eyes will spy on you!\n"
msgstr "Øjne plugin bruger 3D koordianter for at beregne dets øje position, så selvom det nogle gange er uhyggeligt, så vil det øjne nogle gange spionere på dig!\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Netload plugin works with the new udev net interface names and can be configured to show transfer rates in the panel.\n"
msgstr "Netload-pluginet virker med det nye udev net grænseflade navne og kan konfigureres til at vise overførsel rater i panelet.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clipboard manager plugin optionally displays a QR code.\n"
msgstr "Udklipsholder-håndterings plugin har muligheden for at vise QR kode.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cpufreq plugin now supports the intel pstate driver and can adapt better for different panel sizes and information displayed.\n"
msgstr "Cpufreq plugin understøtter nu intel pstadie driver og kan tilpasse bedre for forskellige panel størrelser og information vist.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nearly all plugins have been improved to give the same look and feel and to support the new deskbar panel mode.\n"
msgstr "Næsten all plugins er blevet forbedret til at give same udseende og følelse og samtidig understøttelse ny skrivebord-bar panel-metoden.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "An online tour of the changes in Xfce 4.12 can be viewed here:\n"
msgstr "En onlinerundvisning over ændringerne i Xfce 4.12 kan ses her:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "A detailed overview of the changes between Xfce 4.10 and Xfce 4.12 releases can be found on the following page:\n"
msgstr "Et detaljeret overblik over ændringerne mellem Xfce 4.10 og Xfce 4.12 findes på følgende side:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "A warm thank you all the contributors, translators and packagers for your efforts in making this release possible. We would also like to thank our fantastic users and occasional contributors who submitted bug reports, helped us find issues and sometimes provided patches. We are currently reviewing all patches sent to us and will include many more fixes to Xfce in the next release. We would also like to thank the many people who donated money to our project via Bounty Source. This will help us meet and hack on Xfce in the future!\n"
msgstr "Et varmt tak til alle bidragsydere, oversættere og pakkere for jeres indsats i at lave denne udgivelse muligt. Vi vil også gerne takke vores fantastiske brugere og lejlighedsvis bidragsydere der indsendte fejlretninger, hjalp os med at finde problemer og nogle gange indsendte lapninger/patches. Vi er gennemgår undervejs alle lapninger/patches sendt til os og vil inkludere mange flere rettelse til Xfce in den næste udgave. Vi ville også takke mange af dem som donerede penge til vores projekt via Bounty Source. Dette vil hjælpe os med at møde og hacke på Xfce i fremtiden!\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1425081600.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "As always, we welcome everyone who would like to contribute to the development of Xfce! You can either [test Xfce](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/building) and [report bugs](https://bugzilla.xfce.org), you can help us with [translations](https://www.transifex.com/tag/xfce/) and [documentation](https://docs.xfce.org), with [usability and user experience](https://wiki.xfce.org/design/start) by packaging Xfce into your distribution, and by [submitting patches](https://wiki.xfce.org/dev/howto/contribute) or entirely new features! You can get in touch with us on the Freenode IRC channel #xfce-dev and our [mailing list](https://mail.xfce.org/mailman/listinfo/xfce4-dev).\n"
msgstr ""
"Som altid velkommer vi alle der gerne til bidrage til udviklingen af Xfce!\n"
"Du kan enten [teste Xfce](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/building) og [rapportere fejl](https://bugzilla.xfce.org), du kan hjælpe os med [oversættelser](https://www.transifex.com/tag/xfce/) og [dokumentation](https://docs.xfce.org), med [avendelighed og bruger-oplevelse](https://wiki.xfce.org/design/start)ved at pakke Xfce ind i din distrobution og ved [indsende fejl-retninger](https://wiki.xfce.org/dev/howto/contribute)eller helt nye funktioner! Du kan få fat på os, på Freenode IRC kanalen #xfce-dev og vores [mailing-liste](https://mail.xfce.org/mailman/listinfo/xfce4-dev).\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.10 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.10 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Today, after 1 year and 4 months of work, we are pleased to announce the release of the Xfce desktop 4.10, a new stable version that supersedes Xfce 4.8.\n"
msgstr "I dag, efter 1 år og 4 måneders arbejde, er vi glade for at kunne bekendtgøre udgivelsen af Xfce-skrivebordet 4.10, en ny stabil version som afløser Xfce 4.8.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the 4.10 cycle we mainly focused on polishing the desktop and improving the user experience in various ways. Highlights of this release are:\n"
msgstr "I 4.10 cyklussen fokuserer vi primært på at polere skrivebordet og forbedre bruger-oplevelsen på forskellige måder. Højdepunkterne af denne udgivelse er:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new application finder that has been completely rewritten and combines the functionality of the old xfce4-appfinder and xfrun4.\n"
msgstr "En ny applikations-finder er blevet fuldstændig omskrevet og kombinerer funktionaliteten af den ældre xfce4-appfinder og xfrun4.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "The panel now has an alternative vertical display mode (a deskbar). What is more, panel plugins can be arranged in multiple rows, which is particularly useful in the deskbar mode.\n"
msgstr "Panelet har nu en alternativ vandret visnings-metode (en skrivebar). Hvad ellers, plugins kan nu arrangeres in flere rækker, hvilket især er brugbar i skrivebordsbjælketilstanden.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new MIME type editor that allows you to easily change applications used for opening different file types. The mouse and touchpad settings dialog and the settings editor were extended in terms of functionality. The former now supports tablets in a much better way.\n"
msgstr "En ny MIME type-redigerer der nemt tillader dig at skrive applikationer brugt til at åbne forskellige filtyper. Mus og redskabs-indstillings dialogen og indstillings-redigeren var udvidet med funktionalitet. Den førnævnte understøtter tablet's på en meget bedre måde.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is now possible to launch applications and open files on the desktop with a single click of the mouse. In addition, the 4.10 desktop can display thumbnails and automatically advance through the wallpaper list.\n"
msgstr "Det er nu muligt at køre applikationer og åbne filer på skrivebordet med et enkelt klik på musen. Derudover, 4.10 skrivebordet kan nu vise miniaturer og automatisk avancere gennem baggrundsbillede-listen.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "The window manager can be configured to tile windows when dragging them to the screen edges. The tab window (Alt+Tab) supports more flexible theming and cursor key navigation.\n"
msgstr "Vindue-håndtering kan nu konfigureres til flise vinduer når de trækkes til skærmkanten. Tab vinduet (Alt+Tab) understøtter flere fleksible temaer og markør-nøgle navigation.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "An online tour of the changes in Xfce 4.10 can be viewed here:\n"
msgstr "En onlinerundvisning over ændringerne i Xfce 4.10 kan ses her:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "A detailed overview of the changes compared to Xfce 4.8 and Xfce 4.10 preview releases can be found on the following page:\n"
msgstr "Et detaljeret overblik af ændringer sammenlignet med Xfce 4.8 og Xfce 4.10 forhåndsvisnings-udgaver kan nu findes på følgende side:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1335571200.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Thank you all the contributors, bug reporters, as well as translators and packagers for your efforts in making this release possible.\n"
msgstr "Tak til alle jer bidragsydere, fejl-indsendere, og også oversættere og pakkere for jeres indsats i at gøre denne udgivelse mulig.\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.10pre2 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.10pre2 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Xfce development team is proud to announce the second preview release for Xfce 4.10. Together with this preview release, the Xfce project announces the string and code (only critical bug fixes or regressions) freeze for the final 4.10 release which is set to be pushed out to the world on April 28th, 2012.\n"
msgstr "Xfce-udviklingsholdet er stolt over at kunne annoncere den anden forhåndsviste udgivelse af Xfce 4.10. Sammen med denne forhåndsviste udgave, kan Xfce projektet annoncere streng og kode (kun kritiske fejl-retninger eller regræssioner) Frys for den sidste 4.10 udgave hvilket er sat til at blive udgivet til verdenen den 28 April, 2012.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "This release incorporates some new features like improved responsiveness of file operations in Thunar and tiling improvements in Xfwm4. Everything else is bug fixes and a _lot_ of translation updates.\n"
msgstr "Denne udgivelse inkorporerer nogle nye funktioner som forbedret lydhørhed af fil operationer i Thunar og flise-forbedringer i Xfwm4. All andet er fejl-rettelser og masser_af_oversættelses_opdateringer.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "We hope you will enjoy this release. Please give us feedback by sharing your thoughts, blogging, tweeting or by filing bug reports! With your help, 4.10 will be the best release ever (at least until 4.12)!\n"
msgstr "Vi håber du vil nyde denne udgave. Venligst giv os tilbagemeldinger ved at dele dine tanker, blogge, tweete eller ved at indsende fejl-rapporteringer! Med din hjælp vil 4.10 være den bedste udgave nogensinde (indtil 4.12 udgaven)!\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:16 content/about/news/1333238400.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kind regards and thanks to everyone who has contributed to this release,<br />The Xfce development team\n"
msgstr "Venlige hilsener og tak til alle som har bidraget til denne udgave, <br />Xfce-udviklingsholdet\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.10pre2/)\n"
msgstr "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.10pre2/)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Changes in this release](/download/changelogs/4.10pre2)\n"
msgstr "[Ændringer i denne udgivelse](/download/changelogs/4.10pre2)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1334361600.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Permalink](/about/news/1334361600/)\n"
msgstr "[Permalink](/about/news/1334361600/)\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.10pre1 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.10pre1 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Xfce development team is proud to announce the first preview release for Xfce 4.10. Together with this preview release, the Xfce project announces the feature freeze for the final 4.10 release which is set to be pushed out to the world on April 28th, 2012.\n"
msgstr "Xfce udviklingsholdet er stolte over at kunne annoncere den første forhåndsviste udgave af Xfce 4.10. Sammen med denne forhåndsviste udgave, vil Xfce projektet annoncere frys-funktionen for den endelige 4.10 udgave hvilket er sat til at blive skubbet ud til verdenen April 28'ende 2012.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "This release incorporates major changes to the core of the Xfce desktop environment and hopefully succeeds in fulfilling a number of long time requests. Among the most notable updates is the new application finder that merges the functionality of the old appfinder and xfrun4. The Panel also has a new vertical mode [aka Deskbar] for better space usage on wide-screen monitors and a new actions plugin. On the settings side the settings helper is integrated in xfsettingsd, saving 1 running process. There is also a reworked settings dialog with categories and pluggable dialogs enabled by default. Basic Synaptics and Wacom settings in the Mouse settings and a new MIME-Type editor. Thunar gained a more polished layout to reduce space usage and more responsive interaction with the thumbnail generator. Because we have not decided on how to merge the desktop functionality into Thunar yet, Xfdesktop has instead received various improvements, including single-click support, desktop icon thumbnails and better pasting of files. The Session Manager has improved power management code, tips have been removed and cleanup sessions from the interface. Last but not least, the Window Manager now has support for tiling windows and arrow key navigation in the task switcher.\n"
msgstr ""
"Denne udgave inkorporerer massive ændringer til kernen af Xfce skrivebords-miljøet og forhåbentlig får succes i at opfylde et nummer af langtids-krav. Mellem de mest bemærkelsesværdige opdateringer er den nye applikations-finder der sammenlægger funktionaliteten af den gamle appfinder og xfrun4. Panelet har også en ny vandret-måde [aka Skrivebar] for bedre plads udnyttelse på bredskærme og en ny handling plugin. På indstillingssiden er indstillings-hjælperen integreret i xfsettingsd og dermed redder 1 kørende process. Der er også en omskrevet indstillings-dialog med kategorier og forbinde-bare dialoger aktiveret ved standard. Basis Synaptic og Wacom indstillinger inde i mus-indstillingerne og en ny MIME-Type redigerer. Thunar har fået en mere poleret opsætning for at reducere plads udnyttelse og mere lydhørligheds-interaktion med miniature generatoren.\n"
"Fordi vi ikke endnu har besluttet på hvordan vi sammenlægger skrivebords-funktionalitet ind i Thunar. Xfskrivebordet har istedet modtager forskellige forbedringer, inkluderet enkelt-klik understøttelse, skrivebords-ikon miniature og bedre klistring af filer. Sessions-håndterer er blevet forbedret, strømstyrings-kode, fif er blevet fjernet og rensede sessioner fra brugergrænsefladen. Til sidst har Vindue-Håndtering nu understøttelse for flise-vinduer og piltast navigation i arbejdsområde-skifteren.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Another big change for users is the removal of user documentation of the packages and introduction of [docs.xfce.org](https://docs.xfce.org). The reason for this change is the limited contribution of documentation since Xfce 4.8, so we hope the wiki will attract more contributors. The help buttons in the interface still work, but you'll be asked to open the documentation website in your web browser.\n"
msgstr "En anden stor ændring for brugere er fjernelse af bruger-dokumentation af pakkerne og introduktionen af [docs.xfce.org](https://docs.xfce.org). Grunden for denne ændring er det begrænsede bidrag til dokumentationen siden Xfce 4.8, så vi håber at wiki'en til tiltrække flere bidragsydere. Hjælp knappen i grænsefladen vil stadig virke, men du vil blive spurgt om at åbne dokumentations-hjemmesiden i din internet browser.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Furthermore we dropped xfce-utils. Its content has either been removed or moved to other Xfce packages. All other dependency changes are listed in the 4.10pre1 ChangeLog. The Xfce core also gained a couple of new components because we think they are critical for a minimal desktop: xfce4-power-manager (power management), tumbler (thumbnail generation for Thunar and other components), garcon (menu library, was already a dependency in 4.8), thunar-volman (volume manager for Thunar).\n"
msgstr "Derudover har vi droppet xfce-utils. Dets indhold er enten blevet fjernet eller flyttet til andre Xfce pakker. Alle andre afhængighedes-ændringer er listet inde i 4.10pre1 ÆndringsLog. Xfce kernen har også fået et par nye komponenter fordi we tænker de er kritiske for et minimalt skrivebord: xfce4-strøm-håndtering (strøm-styring), tumber (miniature generatoren til Thunar og andre komponenter), garcon (menu-biblotek, var allerede en afhængighed i 4.8), thunar-volman (lydsstyrke-håndtering for Thunar).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Of course translations also improved a lot, thanks to the amazing work of our translation teams.\n"
msgstr "Selvfølgelig er oversættelserne også forbedret meget, tak til det fantastiske arbejde af vores oversættelses-hold.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "We hope you will enjoy this release. Please give us feedback by sharing your thoughts, blogging, tweeting, denting or by filing bug reports. With your help, 4.10 will be the best release ever (at least until 4.12)!\n"
msgstr "Vi håber du vil nyde denne udgave. Venligst giv os tilbagemeldinger ved at dele dine tanker, blogge, tweete, bule eller ved at indsende fejl-rapporter. Med din hjælp, vil 4.10 være den bedste udgave nogensinde (indtil 4.12 udgives)!\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.10pre1/)\n"
msgstr "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.10pre1/)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Changes in this release](/download/changelogs/4.10pre1)\n"
msgstr "[Ændringer i denne udgivelse](/download/changelogs/4.10pre1)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1333238400.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Permalink](/about/news/1333238400/)\n"
msgstr "[Permalink](/about/news/1333238400/)\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.8 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.8 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Today, after almost two years of work, we have the special pleasure of announcing the much awaited release of Xfce 4.8, the new stable version that supersedes Xfce 4.6.\n"
msgstr "Idag, efter næsten 2 års arbejde, har vi en særlig nydelse af at annoncere den længe ventede udgave af Xfce 4.8, den nye stabile version der overgår Xfce 4.6.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "We hope that everyone will enjoy this release as much as we do. Sadly, this will not be the case as the folks using any of the BSD systems will notice a sudden loss of features. We think that this announcement is a good opportunity to express our disagreement with the recent \"Linux-only\" developments in the open source ecosystem, especially with regards to the utilities we need in desktop environments.\n"
msgstr "Vi håber at alle vil nyde denne udgave, så meget som vi gør. Desværre, vil dette ikke være sagen for de mennesker der bruger nogen af BSD systemerne, der vil opleve pludselig tab af funktioner. Vi tænker at denne annoncering er en god måde mulighed for at udtrykke vores uenighed med de seneste \"kun-Linux\" udviklinger i den åben kildekode økosystem, specielt med hensyn til de værktøjer vi har brug for i skrivebord-miljøer.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.8 is our attempt to update the Xfce code base to all the new desktop frameworks that were introduced in the past few years. We hope that our efforts to drop pieces like ThunarVFS and HAL with GIO, udev, ConsoleKit and PolicyKit will help bringing the Xfce desktop to modern distributions.\n"
msgstr "Xfce 4.8 er vores forsøg på at opdatere Xfce kode-basen til alle nye skrivebords-rammeværk der blev introduceret i de seneste par år. Vi håber at vores indsats med at sætte nogle stykker ned såsom ThunarVFS og HAL med GIO, udev, KonsolKit og Politik-Kit vil hjælpe med at bringe Xfce skrivebordet til moderne distrobutioner.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "With Xfce 4.8 our users will be able to browse remote shares using a variety of protocols (SFTP, SMB, FTP and many more). The window clutter has been reduced by merging all file progress dialogs into a single one.\n"
msgstr "Med Xfce 4.8 er vores brugere i stand til at gennemse fjern-deling ved brug af varierede protokoller (SFTP, SMB, FTP og mange flere). Vinduets uorden er blevet reduceret ved at sammenlægge alle fil-fremskridts dialoger ind i en enkelt én.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our panel application has been rewritten, thereby improving positioning, transparency, item and launcher management. It also introduces a new menu plugin to view directories. Its plugin framework remains compatible with 4.6 plugins.\n"
msgstr "Vores panel applikation er blevet omskrevet og dermed forbedret positionering, gennesigtighed, punkter og kørelse-håndtering. Det introducerer også en ny menu plugin for at se mapper. Dets plugin-rammeværk er stadig kompatibel med 4.6 plugins.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "We also improved our settings dialogs. The display configuration dialog now supports RandR 1.2, detects screens automatically and allows our users to pick their favorite resolution, refresh rate, rotation. Screens can be configured to either work in clone mode or be placed next to each other. Keyboard selection has become easier and more user-friendly. Also, the manual settings editor has been updated to be more functional.\n"
msgstr "Vi har også forbedret vores indstillings-dialoger. Skærm-konfigurationens dialog understøtter RandR 1.2, registrerer skærme automatisk og tillader vores brugere at vælge deres favorit-opløsning, opdateringshastighed, rotation. Skærme kan konfigureres til enten at arbejde i klone-metoden eller blive placeret ved siden af hinanden. Tastatur-selektion er blevet nemmere og mere brugervenligt. Også de manuelle indstillings-redigering er blevet opdateret til at være mere funktionel.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Aside from the features implemented in Xfce, the 4.8 development cycle brought us a bunch of other goodies. For the first time we had a serious release strategy formed after the \"Xfce Release and Development Model\" developed at the Ubuntu Desktop Summit in May 2009. A new web application made release management a lot easier. We worked hard on improving the situation of Xfce translators which led us to setting up our own Transifex server. Something else you will hopefully notice is that our server and mirroring infrastructure has been improved so that our servers hopefully will not suddenly surrender shortly after this release announcement.\n"
msgstr "Udover funktionerne implementeret i Xfce, har 4.8 udviklingen cycklus bragt os en bunke andre lækkerier. For første gang havde vi en seriøs udgivelses-strategi formet efter \"Xfce Udgave og Udviklings Model\" udviklet ved Ubuntu Skrivebord Topmødet i Maj 2009. En ny internet applikation gjorde udgivelses-håndtering meget nemmere. Vi arbejdede hårdt på at forbedre situationen af Xfce oversættere hvilket førte os til at sætte vores egen Transifex server op. Noget andet du forhåbentlig har lagt mærke til er at vores servere og spejlings-infrastruktur er blevet forbedre sådan så vores servere forhåbentlig, ikke overgiver sig kort efter denne udgave-annoncering.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is a lot more to discover and we hope a lot of you will give Xfce 4.8 a try! There is a brief tour online on\n"
msgstr "Der er meget mere at opdage og vi håber mange af jer vil give Xfce 4.8 et forsøg! Der er en kort tour online på\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "A summary of the changes since the 4.8pre3 preview release is available on the following URL (it also includes links to the changes introduced in all preview releases):\n"
msgstr "Et summarum af ændringerne siden 4.8pre3 forhåndsvisnings-udgaven er tilgængelig på følgende URL adresse (det inkluderer også links til ændringerne introduceret i all forhåndsvisnings-udgaverne):\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The release can be downloaded either as individual releases or as a fat tarball including all these individual versions:\n"
msgstr "Udgaven kan hentes fra enten individuelle udgaver eller som en tyk tarball inkluderet alle disse individuelle versioner:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "2011 has just begun and we are already planning for the future. The 4.10 schedule will be worked on soon and hopefully, we will be able to turn Xfce into a non-profit organization at this year's FOSDEM, so stay tuned!\n"
msgstr "Da 2011 var lige begyndt og vi planlagde allerede for fremtiden. 4.10 tidsplanen vil blive arbejdet på snart og forhåbentlig, vil vi være i stand til at vende Xfce ind til en ikke-profit organisation ved dette års FOSDEM, så bliv hængende!\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1295136000.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "But until then we hope you will enjoy today's release and join us in celebrating. Thanks go out to all our contributors, bug reporters as well as the awesome efforts of our translators and packagers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.8pre3 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.8pre3 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Today we are pleased to announce the third and hopefully final preview release of Xfce 4.8 which is set to be pushed out to the public on January 16th, 2011. Compared to Xfce 4.8pre2 this release mostly features translation updates and bug fixes.\n"
msgstr "Idag er vi tilfredse med at annoncere den tredje og forhåbentlig endelige forhånds-udgave af Xfce 4.8 hvilket er sat til at blive skubbet ud til offentligheden Januar d. 16, 2011. Sammenlignet med Xfce 4.8pre2 indeholder denne udgave for det meste oversættelses-opdateringer og fejl-rettelser.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "With christmas and new year's eve between 4.8pre2 and 4.8pre3 it comes as no surprise that for most components only a few issues were tackled.\n"
msgstr "Med jul og nytårsaften mellem 4.8pre2 og 4.8pre3 er det ingen overraskelse at for de fleste komponenter, var det kun et par problemer der blev taklet.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Among other things we updated the default keyboard shortcuts to include monitor keys. The status icon of the file manager's progress dialog is now properly hidden when the dialog is destroyed. Its wallpaper plugin is now capable of handling filenames with spaces. The environment variables of commands launched from the Xfce run dialog were not set properly, so we fixed that so that commands launched from the dialog always inherit the environment of the Xfce session.\n"
msgstr "Blandt andre ting har vi opdateret standard tastatur-genveje til at inkludere skærm-nøgler. Status ikoner af fil-håndtering, udviklings-dialog er nu ordenligt gemt når dialogen er ødelagt. Dets baggrunds-billede plugin er nu i stand til at håndtere filnavne med mellemrum. Miljø-variabler af kommandoer kørt fra Xfce kør-dialogen var ikke sat ordenligt, så vi har rettet det så kommandoer kørt fra dialogen altid arver miljøet af Xfce-sessionen.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "We also made the `--reboot` and `--halt` parameters of xfce4-session-logout work again which previously simply logged out the active user. In order to avoid a race condition at session startup and in order to speed things up a little more we no longer use xrdb to update xft and cursor settings and instead, update the related XSETTINGS properties ourselves.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the window manager xfwm4, we aligned the time period required for a double click with that of normal applications. Via the hidden option /general/mousewheel_rollup one can now disable windows being rolled up via the mouse wheel. The window manager now also properly handles resolution changes in fullscreen windows like those appearing in games. Xfwm4's application switcher now only appears once in cloned mode.\n"
msgstr "I vindue-håndtering xfwm4, har vi opstilt tids-perioden påkrævet for at dobbelt-klikke med normale applikationer. Via den gemte indstilling /general/mousewheel_rollup kan en nu deaktivere vinduer der ruller op via muse-hjulet. Vindue-håndtering har nu også ordenlig håndtering af opløsnings-ændringer i fuld-skærm vinduer som dem der fremgår i spil. Xfwm4's applikations-skifter fremgår nu kun en enkelt gang i klon-måde.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "This may sound like a few useful fixes but it's nothing compared to the amount of work that went into the new Xfce panel once again. Around 20+ known bugs and regressions were fixed. Here is a short excerpt of the complete changelog: Translation domains were fixed for external plugins, plugins can be reordered with DND again, double-clicking items in the item editor shows their preferences, dragging items to the item editor dialog removes them from the panel again, tasklist windows can now be filtered by monitor. Another issue that appeared recently and has now been fixed is the icon sizing in the notification area, also known as the systray.\n"
msgstr "Dette lyder måske som nogle få nyttige rettelser, men det er intet sammenlignet med mængden af arbejdet der er gået ind i Xfce panelet endnu engang. Omkring 20+ kendte fejl og regressioner var rettet. Her is et kort uddrag af den fuldstændige ændringslog: Oversættelses-domæner var rettet for eksterne plugins, plugins kan omorganiseres med DND igen, dobbelt-klikke punkter i elementer i element-redigering viser deres præferencer, trække elementer til element-redigerings dialogen fjerner dem fra panelet igen, jobliste vinduer kan nu filtreres ved brug af skærmen. Endnu et problem der dukkede op for nylig og er nu rettet, er ikon-størrelsesændring i underretningsområdet, også kendt som systray/sysbakke.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.8pre3 also features a lot of translation updates, as can be seen in the complete changelog.\n"
msgstr "Xfce 4.8pre3 inkluderer også mange oversættelses-opdateringer, som kan ses i den fuldstændige ændringslog.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Since we're following the Xfce [release model](/about/releasemodel) for 4.8, we'd normally announce code freeze and the creation of early lifecycle support branches today. We decided against this because there are not enough people active to take care of all this at the moment. So we will continue fixing bugs in master branches as we did between 4.8pre2 and 4.8pre3.\n"
msgstr "Siden vi følger Xfce [udgivelse-model](/about/releasemodel) med 4.8 ville vi normalt annoncere kode-frys og skabelsen af tidlig livs-cyklus understøttelses-grene idag. Vi har valgt imod dette fordi der ikke er nok aktive mennesker til at tage sig af alt dette i øjeblikket. Så vi vil forsætte med at rette fejl, i mester-grenen som vi gjorde mellem 4.8pre2 og 4.8pre3.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.8pre3/)\n"
msgstr "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.8pre3/)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Changes in this release](/download/changelogs/4.8pre3)\n"
msgstr "[Ændringer i denne udgivelse](/download/changelogs/4.8pre3)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1293926400.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Permalink](/about/news/1293926400/)\n"
msgstr "[Permalink](/about/news/1293926400/)\n"

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.8pre2 released"
msgstr "Xfce 4.8pre2 er udgivet"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "We are pleased to announce the second preview release of Xfce 4.8. This release marks the beginning of the string freeze. From today on until the final release, strings may no longer be changed in the master branch of Xfce core components. This will help translators to prepare their translations for the final release scheduled on January 16th, 2011.\n"
msgstr "Vi har fornøjelsen af at annoncere den anden forhåndsviste udgave af Xfce 4.8. Denne udgave markerer begyndelsen af streng-frys. Fra idag til den endelige udgave, streng må ikke længere ændres i mester-grenen af Xfce kerne-komponenter. Dette vil hjælpe oversættere med at forberede deres oversættelser for den endelige udgave d. 16 Januar, 2011.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "For this release we focused on fixing bugs in all Xfce components. We managed to close a great number of them thanks to all the persons who reported them and tested proposed fixes quickly.\n"
msgstr "For denne udgave er vi fokuseret på fejl-rettelser i all Xfce komponenter. Vi har formået at lukke et stort antal af dem takket være alle personerne der rapporterede dem og testede foreslået rettelser hurtigt.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "A few minor panel features were added despite feature freeze. We also managed to work on two long time requests: proper support for editing the application menu with menu editors (Alacarte being the one that we tested) and integration with the Compiz viewport. Of course, this release also features a lot of new and improved translations thanks to the amazing work of our translation teams.\n"
msgstr "Et par mindre panel funktioner var tilføjet, selvom vi var under funktion-frys. Vi har også formået at arbejde på to langtids-andmodninger: ordenlig understøttelse for redigering af applikations-menuen med menu-redigering (Alacarte værende den vi testede) og integration med Compiz udsigts-port. Selvfølgelig har denne udgave også mange nye funktioner og forbedrede oversættelser, tak til det fantastiske arbejde af vores oversættelses-hold.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.8pre2/)\n"
msgstr "[Download](http://archive.xfce.org/xfce/4.8pre2/)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/news/1291507200.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Changes in this release](/download/changelogs/4.8pre2)\n"
msgstr "[Ændringer i denne udgivelse](/download/changelogs/4.8pre2)\n"

